UNITED STATES ex rel. Onofrio IENNA, Relator-Appellant, v. Henry H. CURRAN, as Commissioner, etc., Respondent-Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. December 23, 1926.) No. 157. G. M. Cusumano, of New York City, for appellant. Emory R. Buckner, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Chas. L. Sylvester, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON and HAND, Circuit Judges, and CAMPBELL, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed in open court.
